OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: GUNNISON RIVER - COOPER RANCH
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: THE STATION IS LOCATED ON THE MCINTOSH MOUNTAIN COGUNNISON COUNTY 7.5 MINUTE (TOPOGRAPHIC) QUADRANGLE.  SAMPLING WAS CONDUCTED AT THE GUNNISON RIVER NEAR COOPER RANCH.  MOST OF THE DATA WERE COLLECTED AS PART OF A BASELINE WATER QUALITY INVENTORY FOR THE CURECANTI NATIONAL RECREATION AREA.  THE BASELINE TESTING BEGAN IN 1982 AND CONTINUED UNTIL 1985 WITH SPORADIC TESTING AFTERWARDS.  SOME OF THE DATA WERE COLLECTED PRIOR TO THE CREATION AND DEVELOPMENT OF THE CURECANTI NATIONAL RECREATION AREA AND THE ASSOCIATED RESERVOIRS.  NEARBY AND SIMILAR SAMPLING SITES ARE USED BY THE STATE OF COLORADO DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH; THE U.S. BUREAU OF RECLAMATION; THE EPA; AND THE USGS.  FOR MORE INFORMATION CONTACT THE CHIEF OF RESOURCE MANAGEMENT; CURECANTI NATIONAL RECREATION AREA; 102 ELK CREEK; GUNNISON CO 81230 (TEL. 9706412337).  DATA PROCESSED AND UPLOADED TO STORET BY CURTIS COOPER; NATIONAL PARK SERVICE WATER RESOURCES DIVISION; 1201 OAK RIDGE DRIVE SUITE 250; FORT COLLINS CO 80525 (TEL. 9702253516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Boulder Brook Gage
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The station is located on the Longs Peak CO 7.5' (topographic) series quadrangle in Rocky Mountain National Park.  The station is located at the gage in Boulder Brook along the Boulder Creek Trail south of Bear Lake Rd.  The data originated from a University of Colorado dissertation entitled ""Isotopic and Chemical Flowpath Separation of Streamflow During Snowmelt and Hydrogeological Controls of SurfaceWater Chemistry in Six AlpineSubalpine Basins; Rocky Mountain National Park; Colorado"" 1996 by Julie K. Sueker.  Sueker also contributed other data that weren't included in her dissertation.  For more information about the data; contact Julie K. Sueker; Exponent Environmental Group; 4940 Pearl East Circle Ste. 300; Boulder CO  80301 (Tel. 9704447270).  For information on the park; contact the Chief of Resources at Rocky Mountain National Park; Estes Park CO 80517 (Tel. 970 5861206). OrganizationFormalName: Colorado Dept. of Public Health & Environment
MonitoringLocationName: COLORADO RIVER AT NEW CASTLE
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: A site near New Castle identified as 000047 has been sampled since 1968. The original site was at a bridge west of the town and south of US Hwy 6. The construction of I-70 was in this area was not completed in area until 1971-72. The fate of the original bridge, which is present on a 1962 USGS quad map, is unknown but by 1987 it had been removed. Also unknown is when the site had been moved to its present location near the Coal Ridge Park boat launch on the south bank of the river. Based on the field notes entered in STORET, it appears that the new site has been visited since 1998 but it could be even longer. The two locations are less than a mile apart but Elk Creek flows into the Colorado River just above the old location.

OrganizationFormalName: Colorado Dept. of Public Health & Environment
MonitoringLocationName: NORTH FORK OF THE SOUTH PLATTE BLW. GENEVA CR.
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: From 1997 to 2004, the 5910 site ID was used for samples collected along the North Fork of the South Platte below Geneva Creek. The coordinates, listed in the 2000 draft Master Site List, place the site near the confluence of Geneva Creek near Grant. During the initial 8 years of sampling, the sampling location was progressively moved downstream due to access issues. By November 2003, but possibly earlier, the location for this site coincided with the FY08 sampling location. Aside from the fact that the old and new locations are over a mile apart, there are several potential tributaries and residential developments in that interval that would make these locations distinct. For the FY08 sampling, a new station 5910A was created for the downstream location.

MonitoringLocationName: Glacier Cr - YMCA @ Glacier Cr

Turn right into the YMCA of the Rockies entrance. Take the first left turn onto Mt. Side Dr.  From Mt. Side Dr., follow the signs to Moraine Park. You?uull take a right, then a left. Park under the trees just uphill from the barricades blocking the road. The flowing water within 50 meters is Glacier Creek.  Cross the bridge across Glacier Creek. The sampling site is on river left, upstream of the bridge.

MonitoringLocationName: Big Thompson - YMCA@Big Thompson Valley
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: As you are driving into Estes Park from the east, follow US 34 to US 36 (Moraine). Turn left onto US36. Park under the trees just uphill from the barricades blocking the road. The flowing water within 50 meters is Glacier Creek. Cross the bridge across Glacier Creek and continue on foot, following the signs to Moraine Park. The second bridge cresses the Little Thompson approximately 150 meters up the trail.  The sample site is river left, upstream of the bridge.
